snippet: An International Atomic Energy Agency official said that inspectors had not been given access to a site that they suspect may have been used to test bomb triggers.
abstract: International Atomic Energy Agency says inconclusive talks with Iran led to inspectors not being given access to site that they suspect may have been used to test bomb triggers.
lead_paragraph: An International Atomic Energy Agency official said that inspectors had not been given access to a site that they suspect may have been used to test bomb triggers.

headline.seo: Nuclear Watchdog Says No Accord Reached With Iran
headline.main: Nuclear Watchdog Says No Deal Reached With Iran
headline.print_headline: Nuclear Talks In Iran End With No Pact
